\cf0 	Due to Ilia's main role and semiobvious affection for Link, The Legend of Zelda, Twilight Princess is sometimes referred to as The Legend of Ilia. Indeed, Ilia has a far greater role than Zelda.\
	Here's a quick reference to Ilia's importance.\
- Ilia is the daughter of Ordon Village's Mayor.\
- A brief discussion between Link, Ilia, Ilia's father:\
	\'95 Ilia: Link! You're safe! (Looks at Epona)\
	\'95 Link & Mayor are talking when Ilia shouts: "Look at this! (pointing at Epona's leg) You've hurt her, haven't you?"\
	\'95 Mayor takes side with Link, tells Ilia not to get so angry, or something like that.\
	\'95 Ilia screams something about having every right to be angry and Link needing to take better care of his horse, etc. and storms off with Epona.\
- After Link and Colin explain things to Ilia, she "softens up" and tells Link to come home safely, etc.\
- And then she gets kidnapped.\
- When Link finds her she doesn't know who he is, but knows he's brave, helpful, kind, etc.\
- Link finds some artifact or other which brings back her memory, flashback to spring with Ilia and Link staring at each other (Why? I don't know!) with sweet music (sweet as in beautiful, pretty, high in sugar, etc.) playing\'85\
- Flashback ends, Link and Ilia stand, much as they did in the spring, and Ilia gives Link a horse whistle.\
- And that's about it. Here's what Zelda did.\
- Zelda gave Link info.\
- Possessed Zelda tried to kill Link.\
- Zelda shot Ganondorf with an arrow.\
	Get my point? Yes? Good!
